
[1]saloon

   SALOON', n. [See Hall.]

   In architecture, a lofty spacious hall, vaulted at the top, and usually
   comprehending two stories with two ranges of windows. It is a
   magnificent room in the middle of a building, or at the head of a
   gallery, &c. It is a state room much used in palaces in Italy for the
   reception of embassadors and other visitors.
